Hi, sorry. the MSaccessdb generates this [test](http://www.scaledrop.net/czindia/czindia/image/test.xlsx) file .

Now im trying to use PHPEXCELReader to import this test file into the MYSql database which causes the error
"Export/Import: Invalid number of worksheets, 8 worksheets expected". 
I have used my code for other excel files(not generated by MSaccess) before to upload files and it works, 
the part of code i had to change for importing this file is as follows(for further code i have attached the file)
```
protected function expectedProductsHeading() {
		return array( "SrNo", "ProdType","ItemId", "ProdName", "BrandName","DesignNo", "Colour", "SizeProd", "SaleCode", "MRP", "Quantity", "ImagePath" );
	}



	protected function expectedWorkSheets() {
		return array('Sheet1','Sheet2','Sheet3');
	}
```

I've seen a thing that might help you, that sometimes a file contains extra sheets.
i do something like this as a workaround
$objPHPExcel=PHPExcel_IOFactory::load("file.xlsx");
$reader = new PHPExcel_Reader_Excel2007();
$working_sheet_name_list =$reader->listWorksheetNames"(file.xlsx");
$savesheetnr=$objPHPExcel->getActiveSheetIndex();
$worksheetworkaround= false;
$stepadjust=0;
foreach($objPHPExcel->getSheetNames() as $index=>$name)
{
         foreach($working_sheet_name_list as $keep)
	 {
		if ($name==$keep)
			$worksheetworkaround= true;
	 }
	if ($worksheetworkaround== false)
	 { // delete...
		$index=$index-$stepadjust;
		$objPHPExcel->removeSheetByIndex($index);
		$stepadjust++;
	 }
	$worksheetworkaround= false;
}

This work by that the real sheetsname are found by listWorksheetNames and sheets which sheetnames isn't in that list are removed.

Is that helpning?
